Punch}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{Evobox-1\n|type1=Steel\n|type2=Fairy\n|pictype=art\n|no1=303\n|name1=Mawile\n|type1-1=Steel\n|type2-1=Fairy\n}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Steel|type2=Fairy}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Spritebox/3|ndex=303}}\n{{Spritebox/4|ndex=303}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=303}}\n{{Spritebox/6/2Forms|ndex=303|form1=M}}\n{{Spritebox/7/2Forms|ndex=303|form1=M}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|303|Mawile}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Mawile\'s [[footprint]] is different between the [[Generation III]] games ([[File:F303gen3.png]]) and the [[Generation IV]] games ([[File:F303.png]]).\n* In the 1.0 release of the English version of {{game|Ruby and Sapphire|s|Pokémon Ruby}}, Mawile\'s Pokédex entry incorrectly spells its name twice as \'\'\'MAWHILE\'\'\', not \'\'\'MAWILE\'\'\'. This typo was corrected in version 1.1.\n* Mawile seems to be the counterpart of {{p|Sableye}}. Both of them are {{pkmn2|game-exclusive}} between Ruby and Sapphire as well as {{2v2|HeartGold|SoulSilver}}. They also have the same base stat total (with the same base {{stat|HP}} and {{stat|Speed}} stats), and both have [[Mega Evolution]]s.\n* Mega Mawile has the highest {{stat|Attack}} stat of any Pokémon, with a maximum of 678 (105 base Attack plus {{a|Huge Power}}). This is higher than the limit of 669 Attack (255 base Attack, as 255 is the highest possible 8-digit binary number), and would equal a Pokémon with 259 base Attack.\n** Coincidentally, since it gains {{a|Huge Power}} as an [[Ability]] when it Mega Evolves, Mega Mawile also has the highest stat total increase of all Mega Evolved Pokémon with the equivalent of 205 points instead of the usual 100.\n* Mega Mawile is tied with Mega Sableye for having the lowest [[base stat]] total of all Mega Evolved Pokémon, at 480.\n** Both also have the lowest base HP of all Mega Evolved Pokémon.\n\n===Origin===\n{{bulbanews|On the Origin of Species: Mawile}}\nMawile may have been based on the Japanese legend of the \'\'{{wp|futakuchi-onna}}\'\', a woman with a mouth in the back of her head.\n\n====Name origin====\nMawile is a combination of \'\'{{wp|maw}}\'\' (the mouth of a voracious animal) and \'\'wile\'\' (a stratagem or trick intended to deceive or ensnare).\n\nKucheat is a combination of 口 \'\'kuchi\'\' (mouth) and \'\'cheat\'\' or \'\'eat\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Steel|type2=Fairy\n|ja=クチート \'\'Kucheat\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|口 \'\'kuchi\'\'|mouth}} and \'\'cheat\'\' or \'\'eat\'\'\n|fr=Mysdibule|frmeaning=From {{tt|\'\'mystifier\'\'|to lie}} and {{tt|\'\'mandibule\'\'|mandible}}\n|es=Mawile|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Flunkifer|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Flunkerei\'\'|fib}} and {{tt|\'\'Kiefer\'\'|jaw}}\n|it=Mawile|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=입치트 \'\'Ipchitt\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|입 \'\'ip\'\'|mouth}} and \'\'cheat\'\'\n|zh_cmn=大嘴娃 \'\'Dàzuǐwá\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning= Literally "Big-mouthed doll"\n|hi=मवाइल \'\'Mawile\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Мавайл \'\'Mavayl\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Expedition Society]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Steel|type2=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Steel|prevnum=302|prev=Sableye|nextnum=304|next=Aron}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Single-type Pokémon|303]]<!--Prior to Gen IV-->\n[[Category:Pokémon that have had their type changed]]\n\n[[de:Flunkifer]]\n[[es:Mawile]]\n[[fr:Mysdibule]]\n[[it:Mawile]]\n[[ja:クチート]]\n[[zh:大嘴娃]]'}